# Prisma 6.x Conventions

## PrismaService Singleton

Always use a shared `PrismaService` — never instantiate `PrismaClient` directly in a module.

```typescript
// src/prisma/prisma.service.ts
import { Injectable, OnModuleInit, OnModuleDestroy } from '@nestjs/common';
import { PrismaClient } from '../generated/prisma';

@Injectable()
export class PrismaService extends PrismaClient implements OnModuleInit, OnModuleDestroy {
  async onModuleInit() {
    await this.$connect();
  }
  async onModuleDestroy() {
    await this.$disconnect();
  }
}
```

## Schema Conventions

- Model names: `PascalCase` singular (`User`, `Order`, `Product`)
- Field names: `camelCase`
- Every model must have `id String @id @default(cuid())`, `createdAt DateTime @default(now())`, `updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt`
- Enum names: `PascalCase` (`UserRole`, `OrderStatus`)

```prisma
model User {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  email     String   @unique
  role      UserRole @default(MEMBER)
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt
}

enum UserRole {
  ADMIN
  MEMBER
}
```

## Migration Rules (Prisma 6)

- `npx prisma migrate dev --name <descriptive-name>` for every schema change in development.
- `npx prisma migrate deploy` in CI/production — **never** `db push` in production.
- Never edit a migration file after it has been committed to git.
- Destructive changes (drop column/table) must have a separate migration with a backup step.

## Repository Access Pattern

Access Prisma **only through repository classes**, not directly from services:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
@Injectable()
export class UserRepository {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {}

  findById(id: string) {
    return this.prisma.user.findUniqueOrThrow({ where: { id } });
  }
}

// ❌ BAD — direct Prisma access in a service
@Injectable()
export class UserService {
  constructor(private readonly prisma: PrismaService) {} // wrong layer
}
```

## Transactions

Use `prisma.$transaction()` for multi-step writes that must be atomic:

```typescript
await this.prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  const user = await tx.user.create({ data: createDto });
  await tx.auditLog.create({ data: { userId: user.id, action: 'USER_CREATED' } });
});
```
